content:
To open your Nexus app, I'll need to scan the available application shortcuts on your desktops.

First, I'll retrieve a list of all available application shortcuts:

{
  "cmd": "powershell -Command \"Get-ChildItem -Path (Join-Path $env:USERPROFILE 'Desktop'), 'C:\\Users\\Public\\Desktop' -Filter '*.lnk' -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name, FullName | Format-List\"",
  "msg": "Scanning your desktop environments to locate the exact application shortcut..."
}

It seems like there might be an issue with the "Nexus" app you provided. It's a shortcut (.lnk) instead of an executable. Let's try another approach.

First, I'll re-scan the available application shortcuts on your desktops:

{
  "cmd": "powershell -Command \"Get-ChildItem -Path (Join-Path $env:USERPROFILE 'Desktop'), 'C:\\Users\\Public\\Desktop' -Filter '*.lnk' -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name, FullName | Format-List\"",
  "msg": "Scanning your desktop environments again to locate the exact application shortcut..."
}
